article.headline: E. Kentucky 64, SE Missouri 52
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Josh Daniel scored 19 points and Joshua Jones had 15 as Eastern Kentucky defeated Southeast Missouri 64-52 Saturday. Spencer Perrin added 10 points for the Colonels (9-9, 4-4 Ohio Valley), who have won six straight over the Redhawks. Cameron Butler finished with 10 points and 10 rebounds for Southeast Missouri (5-13, 4-4) while Anthony Allison scored 12 points, and Leon Powell had 11. After Powell's layup with 6:44 to play gave the Redhawks their only lead, 47-46, Eastern Kentucky pulled away for good with an 16-3 run, fueled by 10 points from Daniel. The Colonels built an 11-point early in the first half and went into intermission up 27-24 after Southeast Missouri ended the half with a 6-0 run.
